Title: Laminar and columnar distribution of geniculo-cortical fibers in the macaque monkey
Comments: The connectional data are from lesion studies, that is the reason that they are not entered to the database

@InterMapRelations.Citation: „Nissl- (cresyl-violett) and myelin (Loyez) stained sections through the striate cortex (area 17) of Macaque monkey to show the layering system used in this paper. The Nissl stain shows three cell-sparse regions, layers I, IVb and V, and three cell-dense regions, layers II, III and IVa collectively, layer IVc, and layer VI. The line of Genari is located in layer IVb.”
